OL,3,CDemand for temporary accommodation
OL,4,C'squeezing homelessness services'
OL,6,FThe rising demand for temporary
OL,7,Faccommodation will potentially put
OL,8,Funsustainable pressure on homelessness
OL,9,Fservices in Northern Ireland, the
OL,10,FAuditor General has found.
OL,12,FThe demand has gone up by 176%,
OL,13,Faccording to a report, with 4,700
OL,14,Fhouseholds in temporary accommodation
OL,15,Fin 2023/24, up from 1,700 in 2017.
OL,17,FThe report by Auditor General Dorinnia
OL,18,FCarville found that dealing with the
OL,19,F"unprecedented demand" cost the
OL,20,FHousing Executive almost #39 million
OL,21,Fin 2023-24.
