OL,3,CDemand for temporary accommodation
OL,4,C'squeezing homelessness services'
OL,6,FIt has identified a need for almost
OL,7,F25,000 new social houses between 2023
OL,8,Fand 2028, however current rates of
OL,9,Ffunding and capacity issues mean that
OL,10,Fnew starts are falling considerably
OL,11,Fbelow the level required.
OL,13,FIt was found that allocations to
OL,14,Fsocial housing are not keeping pace
OL,15,Fwith the level of demand, and since
OL,16,F2017 the number of homeless households
OL,17,Fon the social housing waiting list has
OL,18,Fincreased by 81%, with 12,000 of these
OL,19,Fhouseholds having been on the waiting
OL,20,Flist for more than four years.
